Former Colorado State guard and 2017 Mountain West Player of the Year Gian Clavell has agreed to a contract with the Dallas Mavericks. The 6-foot-4, 185 pound guard led the Mountain West in scoring at 20.4 points per-game last season and recently competed with the Miami Heat in both the 2017 NBA Orlando and Las Vegas summer leagues.

The specific details of the contract are still being negotiated between Clavell’s agent and the Mavericks, but the former CSU standout agreed to principal terms with the team on Wednesday. According to ESPN
